5. Correlation Analysis

In[27]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# Select important lab features
lab_features = ["TSH", "T3", "TT4", "T4U", "FTI"]

# Drop missing values temporarily for correlation calculation
lab_df = df[lab_features].dropna()

# Compute correlation matrix
corr_matrix = lab_df.corr()

# Plot heatmap
plt.figure(figsize=(8,6))

sns.heatmap(
    corr_matrix,
    annot=True,          # show correlation values
    cmap="coolwarm",     # color map
    fmt=".2f",           # format numbers
    linewidths=0.5
)

plt.title("Correlation Heatmap of Thyroid Laboratory Parameters", fontsize=14)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

Heatmap Summary

The correlation analysis confirms expected medical relationships:

  • TSH is negatively correlated with thyroid hormones.
  • TT4 and FTI show strong positive correlation.
  • T3 moderately correlates with TT4.

These findings validate the clinical reliability of the dataset.

numerical_cols = ['age', 'TSH', 'T3', 'TT4', 'T4U', 'FTI', 'TBG']

stats_summary = df[numerical_cols].describe().T

# Add additional statistics
stats_summary['median'] = df[numerical_cols].median()
stats_summary['missing_count'] = df[numerical_cols].isna().sum()
stats_summary['missing_pct'] = (df[numerical_cols].isna().sum() / len(df) * 100).round(2)

# Reorder columns for better readability

# 1.4 DTECTION D'ANOMALIES (OUTLIERS)
# ============================================================
print("\n" + "="*80)
print(" 1.4 DTECTION D'ANOMALIES (OUTLIERS)")
print("="*80)

def detect_outliers_iqr(data):
    """Detect outliers using IQR method"""
    Q1 = data.quantile(0.25)
    Q3 = data.quantile(0.75)
    IQR = Q3 - Q1
    lower_bound = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
    upper_bound = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR
    outliers = data[(data < lower_bound) | (data > upper_bound)]
    return outliers, lower_bound, upper_bound

print("\n Analyse des Outliers (Mthode IQR):")

outlier_summary = []

for col in numerical_cols:
    data = df[col].dropna()
    outliers, lower, upper = detect_outliers_iqr(data)
    
    outlier_summary.append({
        'Variable': col,
        'N_Total': len(data),
        'N_Outliers': len(outliers),
        'Pct_Outliers': (len(outliers) / len(data) * 100),
        'Lower_Bound': lower,
        'Upper_Bound': upper,
        'Min_Outlier': outliers.min() if len(outliers) > 0 else np.nan,
        'Max_Outlier': outliers.max() if len(outliers) > 0 else np.nan
    })
    
    print(f"\n{col}:")
    print(f"   Total valeurs:     {len(data)}")
    print(f"   Outliers dtects: {len(outliers)} ({len(outliers)/len(data)*100:.2f}%)")
    print(f"   Limites:           [{lower:.2f}, {upper:.2f}]")

outlier_df = pd.DataFrame(outlier_summary)
outlier_df.to_csv('../data/outliers_summary.csv', index=False)
print("\n Saved: ../data/outliers_summary.csv")

# Visualization
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(14, 6))

colors = ['#e74c3c' if x > 10 else '#f39c12' if x > 5 else '#2ecc71' 
         for x in outlier_df['Pct_Outliers']]

ax.bar(outlier_df['Variable'], outlier_df['Pct_Outliers'], 
       color=colors, alpha=0.7, edgecolor='black')
ax.set_xlabel('Variable', fontweight='bold', fontsize=12)
ax.set_ylabel('Pourcentage d\'Outliers (%)', fontweight='bold', fontsize=12)
ax.set_title('Dtection d\'Outliers par Variable (Mthode IQR)', fontweight='bold', fontsize=14)
ax.grid(True, alpha=0.3, axis='y')

# Add value labels
for i, (var, pct) in enumerate(zip(outlier_df['Variable'], outlier_df['Pct_Outliers'])):
    ax.text(i, pct + 0.5, f'{pct:.1f}%', ha='center', fontweight='bold')

plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig('../plots/03_outliers_detection.png', dpi=300, bbox_inches='tight')

# Identify strong correlations
print("\n Corrlations Fortes (|r| > 0.7):")
strong_corr = []
for i in range(len(corr_matrix.columns)):
    for j in range(i+1, len(corr_matrix.columns)):
        if abs(corr_matrix.iloc[i, j]) > 0.7:
            strong_corr.append({
                'Var1': corr_matrix.columns[i],
                'Var2': corr_matrix.columns[j],
                'Correlation': corr_matrix.iloc[i, j]
            })
            print(f"   {corr_matrix.columns[i]}  {corr_matrix.columns[j]}: {corr_matrix.iloc[i, j]:.3f}")

format_issues = []

# Binary columns
binary_cols = ['on_thyroxine', 'query_on_thyroxine', 'on_antithyroid_meds', 
               'sick', 'pregnant', 'thyroid_surgery', 'I131_treatment',
               'query_hypothyroid', 'query_hyperthyroid', 'lithium', 
               'goitre', 'tumor', 'hypopituitary', 'psych']

print("\n Colonnes binaires (t/f):")
binary_ok = 0
for col in binary_cols:
    unique_vals = set(df[col].dropna().unique())
    expected = {'t', 'f'}
    
    if unique_vals.issubset(expected):
        binary_ok += 1
    else:
        unexpected = unique_vals - expected
        print(f"    {col}: valeurs invalides {list(unexpected)}")
        format_issues.append({'Column': col, 'Issue': f'Invalid: {list(unexpected)}'})

print(f"    {binary_ok}/{len(binary_cols)} colonnes binaires correctes")

# Sex column
print("\n Colonne 'sex':")
sex_values = set(df['sex'].dropna().unique())
expected_sex = {'M', 'F'}
invalid_sex = df[(~df['sex'].isin(['M', 'F'])) & (df['sex'].notna())]

print(f"   Valeurs trouves: {list(sex_values)}")
print(f"   Valeurs manquantes: {df['sex'].isna().sum()} ({df['sex'].isna().sum()/len(df)*100:.1f}%)")

if len(invalid_sex) > 0:
    print(f"    {len(invalid_sex)} valeurs invalides!")
    format_issues.append({'Column': 'sex', 'Issue': f'{len(invalid_sex)} invalid values'})
else:
    print(f"    Format correct")

# Age validation (STRICT)
print("\n Colonne 'age':")
negative_age = df[df['age'] < 0]
zero_age = df[df['age'] == 0]
unrealistic_age = df[df['age'] > 120]
suspicious_age = df[df['age'] > 100]

print(f"   ges ngatifs (< 0):    {len(negative_age)}")
print(f"   ges = 0:               {len(zero_age)} {' Suspect' if len(zero_age) > 0 else ''}")
print(f"   ges > 120:             {len(unrealistic_age)}")
print(f"   ges 100-120:           {len(suspicious_age) - len(unrealistic_age)} {'  vrifier' if len(suspicious_age) > len(unrealistic_age) else ''}")

if len(negative_age) > 0:
    print(f"    CRITIQUE: {len(negative_age)} ges ngatifs!")
    print(f"   Exemples: {negative_age['age'].head().tolist()}")
    format_issues.append({'Column': 'age', 'Issue': f'{len(negative_age)} negative ages'})

if len(unrealistic_age) > 0:
    print(f"    {len(unrealistic_age)} ges > 120 ans!")
    print(f"   Exemples: {unrealistic_age['age'].sort_values(ascending=False).head().tolist()}")
    format_issues.append({'Column': 'age', 'Issue': f'{len(unrealistic_age)} ages >120'})

# Lab values (STRICT)
print("\n Paramtres de laboratoire:")
lab_cols = ['TSH', 'T3', 'TT4', 'T4U', 'FTI']

for col in lab_cols:
    negative = df[df[col] < 0]
    zero = df[df[col] == 0]
    
    if len(negative) > 0:
        print(f"    {col}: {len(negative)} valeurs ngatives!")
        print(f"      Exemples: {negative[col].head().tolist()}")
        format_issues.append({'Column': col, 'Issue': f'{len(negative)} negative'})
    elif len(zero) > 0:
        print(f"    {col}: {len(zero)} valeurs = 0 (biologiquement impossible)")
        format_issues.append({'Column': col, 'Issue': f'{len(zero)} zero values'})
    else:
        print(f"    {col}: OK (toutes valeurs > 0)")

    pregnant_male = pregnant_patients[pregnant_patients['sex'] == 'M']
    pregnant_unknown = pregnant_patients[pregnant_patients['sex'].isna()]
    
    print(f"    Fminin (F):  {len(pregnant_female)} ")
    print(f"    Masculin (M): {len(pregnant_male)} {' CRITIQUE' if len(pregnant_male) > 0 else ''}")
    print(f"    Inconnu:      {len(pregnant_unknown)} {'' if len(pregnant_unknown) > 0 else ''}")
    
    if len(pregnant_male) > 0:
        print(f"\n    VIOLATION CRITIQUE: {len(pregnant_male)} hommes enceints!")
        logical_violations.append({
            'Rule': 'pregnant=t  sex=F',
            'Violations': len(pregnant_male),
            'Severity': 'CRITICAL'
        })
        print("\n   Exemples:")
        print(pregnant_male[['patient_id', 'age', 'sex', 'pregnant']].head().to_string(index=False))
    
    if len(pregnant_unknown) > 0:
        print(f"\n    WARNING: {len(pregnant_unknown)} enceintes sans sexe dfini")
        logical_violations.append({
            'Rule': 'pregnant=t  sex defined',
            'Violations': len(pregnant_unknown),
            'Severity': 'MEDIUM'
        })
else:
    print("    OK: Aucun patient marqu enceinte")

else:

# Rule 3: on_thyroxine=t  TSH measured
print("\n Rgle 3: on_thyroxine='t'  TSH mesur")
on_thyroxine = df[df['on_thyroxine'] == 't']

print(f"   Patients sous thyroxine:   {len(on_thyroxine)}")

if len(on_thyroxine_no_tsh) > 0:

    print(f"\n    WARNING: {pct:.1f}% sans suivi TSH")

    })

# Rule 4: TSH < 0.1  indication hyperthyroid (AMLIOR)
print("\n Rgle 4: TSH < 0.1  indication hyperthyrodie")
very_low_tsh = df[df['TSH'] < 0.1]

# Check if hyperlabel exists
if 'hyperlabel' in df.columns:

    indicator_col = 'hyperlabel'
else:

print(f"   Patients TSH < 0.1:        {len(very_low_tsh)}")

if len(very_low_no_hyper) > 0:

    print(f"\n    WARNING: {pct:.1f}% sans diagnostic appropri")

    logical_violations.append({

print(" 2.4 DTECTION D'ABERRATIONS (SEUILS CLINIQUES RALISTES)")

# Refined clinical ranges
clinical_ranges = {
    'age': {
        'normal': (0, 100),
        'extreme': (0, 120),
        'description': 'ge humain raliste'
    },
    'TSH': {
        'normal': (0.4, 4.0),      # Normal clinical range
        'acceptable': (0.001, 10.0), # Extended range
        'extreme': (0, 50.0),        # Biological limit
        'description': 'TSH (mIU/L)'
    },
    'T3': {
        'normal': (0.8, 2.0),
        'acceptable': (0.4, 4.0),
        'extreme': (0.05, 10.0),
        'description': 'T3 (ng/mL)'
    },
    'TT4': {
        'normal': (50, 150),
        'acceptable': (20, 200),
        'extreme': (5, 400),
        'description': 'TT4 (g/dL)'
    },
    'T4U': {
        'normal': (0.7, 1.3),
        'acceptable': (0.5, 2.0),
        'extreme': (0.1, 3.0),
        'description': 'T4U (ratio)'
    },
    'FTI': {
        'normal': (50, 150),
        'acceptable': (20, 200),
        'extreme': (5, 400),
        'description': 'FTI (Free Thyroxine Index)'
    }
}

aberrations = []

print("\n Analyse avec seuils cliniques ralistes:\n")

for param, ranges in clinical_ranges.items():
    if param not in df.columns:
        continue
        
    data = df[param].dropna()
    
    # Count by ranges
    if 'normal' in ranges:
        in_normal = df[(df[param] >= ranges['normal'][0]) & (df[param] <= ranges['normal'][1])]
        
        if 'acceptable' in ranges:
            in_acceptable = df[(df[param] >= ranges['acceptable'][0]) & (df[param] <= ranges['acceptable'][1])]
            out_acceptable = df[(df[param] < ranges['acceptable'][0]) | (df[param] > ranges['acceptable'][1])]
        else:
            in_acceptable = in_normal
            out_acceptable = pd.DataFrame()
        
        if 'extreme' in ranges:
            beyond_extreme_low = df[df[param] < ranges['extreme'][0]]
            beyond_extreme_high = df[df[param] > ranges['extreme'][1]]
        else:
            beyond_extreme_low = pd.DataFrame()
            beyond_extreme_high = pd.DataFrame()
    else:
        # Only extreme range
        in_acceptable = df[(df[param] >= ranges['extreme'][0]) & (df[param] <= ranges['extreme'][1])]
        beyond_extreme_low = df[df[param] < ranges['extreme'][0]]
        beyond_extreme_high = df[df[param] > ranges['extreme'][1]]
    
    print(f"\n {param} - {ranges['description']}")
    
    if 'normal' in ranges:
        print(f"   Plage normale:      [{ranges['normal'][0]}, {ranges['normal'][1]}]")
        print(f"    Dans la norme:   {len(in_normal)} ({len(in_normal)/len(data)*100:.1f}%) ")
    
    if 'acceptable' in ranges:
        print(f"   Plage acceptable:   [{ranges['acceptable'][0]}, {ranges['acceptable'][1]}]")
        print(f"    Acceptable:      {len(in_acceptable)} ({len(in_acceptable)/len(data)*100:.1f}%) ")
        print(f"    Hors acceptable: {len(out_acceptable)} ({len(out_acceptable)/len(data)*100:.1f}%) ")
    
    if 'extreme' in ranges:
        print(f"   Limites extrmes:   [{ranges['extreme'][0]}, {ranges['extreme'][1]}]")
        
    if len(beyond_extreme_low) > 0:
        print(f"    Aberrant (bas):  {len(beyond_extreme_low)} ({len(beyond_extreme_low)/len(data)*100:.2f}%) ")
        print(f"      Exemples: {beyond_extreme_low[param].sort_values().head(3).tolist()}")
        aberrations.append({
            'Parameter': param,
            'Type': 'Extreme Low',
            'Count': len(beyond_extreme_low),
            'Threshold': ranges['extreme'][0] if 'extreme' in ranges else ranges['acceptable'][0]
        })
    
    if len(beyond_extreme_high) > 0:
        print(f"    Aberrant (haut): {len(beyond_extreme_high)} ({len(beyond_extreme_high)/len(data)*100:.2f}%) ")
        print(f"      Exemples: {beyond_extreme_high[param].sort_values(ascending=False).head(3).tolist()}")
        aberrations.append({
            'Parameter': param,
            'Type': 'Extreme High',
            'Count': len(beyond_extreme_high),
            'Threshold': ranges['extreme'][1] if 'extreme' in ranges else ranges['acceptable'][1]
        })

print("\n" + "-"*80)

# Calculate totals

total_logical = sum([v['Violations'] for v in logical_violations])
total_aberrations = sum([a['Count'] for a in aberrations])
total_issues = total_format + total_logical + total_aberrations

print("\n" + "="*80)
print(" RSUM FINAL")
print("="*80)

print(f"\n Problmes dtects:")
print(f"   Format:       {total_format}")
print(f"   Logique:      {total_logical}")
print(f"   Aberrations:  {total_aberrations}")
print(f"   ")
print(f"   TOTAL:        {total_issues}")

quality_score = max(0, 100 - (total_issues / len(df) * 100))
print(f"\n SCORE DE QUALIT: {quality_score:.2f}/100")

if quality_score >= 95:
    print("    EXCELLENT")
elif quality_score >= 90:
    print("    BON")
elif quality_score >= 80:
    print("    MOYEN")
else:
    print("    FAIBLE")

print("\n" + "="*80)
